1. *Čovek* je najrazvijenija vrsta na planeti. (Man is the most developed species on the planet.) 
2. Moj *muž* je visok i mršav. (My husband is tall and skinny.) 
3. Ova *čaša* je napravljena od stakla. (This glass is made of glass.) 
4. Upravo sam pročitala knjigu o jednom vrlo hrabrom *čoveku*. (I just read a book about a very brave man.) 
5. *Ljudi* često donose odluke na osnovu emocija, umesto razuma. (People often make decisions based on emotions instead of reason.) 
6. Koliko *novca* treba da bih kupio taj automobil? (How much money do I need to buy that car?) 
7. *Dečak* se igra u parku sa svojim prijateljima. (The boy is playing in the park with his friends.) 
8. Sinoć sam sanjao neobičan san o *čudnom čoveku*. (Last night, I had a strange dream about a strange man.) 
9. *Gospodin* Petrović je veoma uspešan biznismen. (Mr. Petrović is a very successful businessman.) 
10. Mama je ispekla najukusnije *kolače* koje sam ikada probao. (Mom baked the most delicious cakes I've ever tasted.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "man" can be translated as "čovek" or "muškarac," depending on the context. However, "muškarac" is a more specific term and refers specifically to an adult male, while "čovek" can refer to a human being in general.